        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 8:07AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 806 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sterling City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
